# Server Patterns

## Route handlers

- One router per domain: `products`, `contact`, `quotes`, `admin`.
- Wrap async handlers in try/catch, call `next(err)` on failure.
- Validate request bodies with Zod at the top of the handler; return 400 on validation error.
- Use `.lean()` for read-only queries.

## Admin routes

- All admin routes behind `adminAuth` middleware (JWT verification).
- Login endpoint validates `ADMIN_SECRET` and returns a signed JWT.
- Paginate list endpoints with `page` and `limit` query params.

## Models

- Mongoose schemas in `src/models/`. Export both the interface (`IProduct`) and the model (`Product`).
- Use `timestamps: true` for automatic `createdAt`/`updatedAt`.
- Add indexes on frequently queried fields (`partNumber`, `manufacturer`).

## Services

- `src/services/email.ts` — Resend integration. Gracefully skip if `RESEND_API_KEY` is empty.
- `src/services/cloudinary.ts` — Upload/delete. Gracefully skip if `CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` is empty.
- Fire-and-forget email sending (`.catch(console.error)`) to avoid blocking the response.

## Error handling

- Central `errorHandler` middleware in `src/middleware/errorHandler.ts`.
- Return `{ error: string }` shape for all error responses.
